title: Rolling Heights
text:
Rolling Heights is an <a href="unincorporated%20area">unincorporated community</a> in <a href="Alberta">Alberta</a>, Canada within <a href="Parkland%20County">Parkland County</a> that is recognized as a <a href="designated%20place">designated place</a> by <a href="Statistics%20Canada">Statistics Canada</a>. It is located on the east side of <a href="Alberta%20Highway%20779">Highway 779</a>, north of <a href="Alberta%20Highway%2016">Highway 16</a>.
Demographics.
As a designated place in the <a href="Canada%202016%20Census">2016 Census of Population</a> conducted by <a href="Statistics%20Canada">Statistics Canada</a>, Rolling Heights recorded a population of 132 living in 38 of its 38 total private dwellings, a change of from its 2011 population of 139. With a land area of , it had a population density of in 2016.
As a designated place in the <a href="Canada%202011%20Census">2011 Census</a>, Rolling Heights had a population of 139 living in 38 of its 40 total dwellings, a 2.2% change from its 2006 population of 136. With a land area of , it had a population density of in 2011.
